<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
In Japanese this sentence pattern is used to express the idea of comparison.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{stone^rice*field}}san'no<strong>houga</strong>@KJ{{private}}<strong>yori</strong>@KJ{{young}}idesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Mr. ishida is younger than I am.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
The @HI{{yori}} part can come before the @HI{{houga}} part.
</p>

<p>
The @HI{{houga}} part is not always necessary.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{grove}}sanha@KJ{{private}}<strong>yori</strong>@KJ{{quick}}ku@KJ{{run}}reru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Mr. Hayashi can run faster than I can.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

